data.name: label15.Text
data.value: Given n rectangular buildings in a 2-dimensional city, computes the skyline of these buildings, eliminating hidden lines. All buildings share common bottom and every building is represented by triplet (left, ht, right) Output should be skyline: A skyline is a collection of rectangular strips. A rectangular strip is represented as a pair (left, ht) where left is x coordinate of left side of strip and ht is height of strip.

data.name: label9.Text
data.value: Given an arbitrary Binary Tree. Convert to a tree that holds Children Sum Property You can only increment data values in any node, (You cannot change structure of tree and cannot decrement value of any node).

data.name: label12.Text
data.value: You are given a node which has value, weight and its parent. Print out, for each node, the total weight of a subtree below this node (by convention, the weight of a subtree for node X includes the own weight of X).
